         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">21/1/65. ¶ Dear Prof. Lindley ¶  ¶ I beg to offer to you a proofplate of Gastrolobium grandiflorum, the poison-plant, discovered by J. M. Stuart near Attack Creek in N. W. Australia and which since ha...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">65.01.21a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Lindley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Cambridge University Herbarium, World Collection, Australia folder <name key="Gastrolobium%20grandiflorum">Gastrolobium grandiflorum</name> F. Muell., (B&amp;H) 57.22.18.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Gastrolobium%20grandiflorum">Gastrolobium grandiflorum</name>
                     </seg>.</p>
               </note>21/1/65.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Prof. Lindley</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I beg to offer to you a proofplate of <name key="Gastrolobium%20grandiflorum">Gastrolobium grandiflorum</name>, the poison-plant, discovered by J. M. Stuart near Attack Creek in N. W. Australia and which since has proved so destructive to flocks in the interior of Queensland between the Suttor River and the sources of the Flinders River.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to the </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gardeners' chronicle and agricultural gazette</seg>
                     <seg style="">, 25 July 1864 (in this edition as 64-07-25c).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> It is, as you will be aware, the only Gastrolobium, hitherto found out of the limits of N. W. Australia.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The fourth volume of the fragmenta, of which this plate is one, will I hope be transmitted for your kind acceptance by next mail, as well, as a volume of illustrations of Victorian plants.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B65.13.04.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With profound regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Filed with the MS is a proof of an etching of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Gastrolobium%20grandiflorum">Gastrolobium grandiflorum</name>
                     </seg>, annotated by M: 'The recently discovered poison-plant of Queensland and N. W. Australia'. The plate was published in M's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Fragmenta</seg>, vol. 4, p. 174, where M also noted the occurrence of the species near the source of the Flinders River; he had previously described the species from a specimen collected near Attack Creek, NT, by John McDouall Stuart, in B62.04.01, p. 17.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Gastrolobium%20grandiflorum">Gastrolobium grandiflorum</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
